hs and replace them with [[open-road tolling]] (officially called ''Multi-Lane Free Flow'', MLFF by the government) similar to the [[Electronic Toll Collection (Taiwan)|ETC system in Taiwan]].\n\n== Europe ==\n\n=== Western Europe ===\n* Austria \u2013 [[Videomaut]] for motorways and expressways subject to special tolls\n* Austria \u2013 [[go-maut]]<ref>{{cite web|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140206053706/http://www.go-maut.at/|title=Startseite - GO Maut|author=|archive-date=6 February 2014|website=web.archive.org|accessdate=15 May 2019|url=http://www.go-maut.at/}}</ref> for the national [[Autobahn]] network\n* Belgium \u2013 Kilometer charge for trucks on public roads<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.viapass.be/en/|title=ViaPass - ViaPass|last=ViaPass|website=www.viapass.be}}</ref>\n* France \u2013 T\u00e9l\u00e9p\u00e9age, usually branded [[liber-t]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.saneftolling.co.uk|title=Sanef Tolling|website=Sanef Tolling}}</ref> on motorways (run by the Federation of French Motorway Companies) (ASFA)\n* Germany \u2013 [[LKW-MAUT]] for trucks on [[Autobahns]]\n* Italy \u2013 [[TELEPASS]] on [[Autostrade]] motorways\n* Portugal \u2013 [[Via Verde]]\n* Portugal \u2013 Highways A22 (Algarve) and A28 (Porto) operated by Via Livre<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vialivre.pt|title=Vialivre|first=Vialivre|last=S.A.|website=www.vialivre.pt}}</ref>\n* Spain \u2013 VIA-T,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.viat.es|title=Inicio - Via-t Sistema de Telepeaje|website=www.viat.es}}</ref> VIA-T Pagatelia,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pagatelia.com/|title=VIA T mobe\u00ae \u2022 el telepeaje m\u00e1s barato \u00b7 Pagatelia|website=www.pagatelia.com}}</ref> VIA-T Bip&Drive<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bipdrive.com/es/|title=Via-T Bip&Drive \u2022 Telepeaje en autopistas de Espa\u00f1a, Francia y Portugal|website=Bip&Drive|access-date=2014-12-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141222135522/http://www.bipdrive.com/es/|archive-date=2014-12-22|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* Switzerland \u2013 performance-related heavy vehicle fee<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ezv.admin.ch/zollinfo_firmen/steuern_abgaben/00379/index.html?lang=en |title=Archived copy |access-date=2011-02-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110223140001/http://www.ezv.admin.ch/zollinfo_firmen/steuern_abgaben/00379/index.html?lang=en |archive-date=2011-02-23 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n=== United Kingdom and Ireland ===\n* Ireland \u2013 [[eToll]] national standard\n* Ireland \u2013 [[Eazy Pass]] [[National Toll Roads]] implementation of eToll\n* United Kingdom \u2013 [[Dartford Crossing#Dart-Tag|Dart-Tag]] for the [[Dartford Crossing]]\n* United Kingdom \u2013 [[London congestion charge]] in [[London]]\n* United Kingdom \u2013 [[Fast tag]]  Mersey tunnels: [[Queensway Tunnel]] and [[Kingsway Tunnel]]\n* United Kingdom \u2013 [[M6 Toll tag]] in the [[English Midlands|Midlands]]\n* United Kingdom \u2013 [[Severn TAG]] for the [[Severn Bridge]] crossing and [[Second Severn Crossing]]\n* United Kingdom \u2013 [[Tamar Bridge]]\n* United Kingdom \u2013 permit for the [[Tyne Tunnel]] linking North and South [[Tyneside]]\n* United Kingdom \u2014 HumberTag, used on the [[Humber Bridge]] in [[North Lincolnshire]] and the [[East Riding of Yorkshire]]\n\n=== Scandinavia ===\n* Denmark/Sweden \u2013 [[BroBizz]] ([[EasyGo]]) for the [[Oresund bridge|\u00d8resund]], [[Great Belt Bridge|Great Belt]] and Crown Princess Mary's bridges\n* Norway \u2013 [[AutoPASS]] ([[EasyGo]])<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.autopass.no/newsread/news.asp?N=5012&L=1 |title=Archived copy |access-date=2008-05-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050409202512/http://www.autopass.no/newsread/news.asp?N=5012&L=1 |archive-date=2005-04-09 |url-status=dead }}</ref> on some ferries and all [[Toll roads in Norway|toll roads]] except the [[Atlantic Ocean Tunnel]]\n* Sweden \u2013 [[Stockholm congestion tax]] in [[Stockholm]], [[Gothenburg congestion tax]] in [[Gothenburg]] and infrastructure charge on Motala and Sundsvall bridges<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.epass24.com/road-tolls/swedish-road-tolls|title=EPASS24|website=www.epass24.com}}</ref>\n\n=== Eastern Europe ===\n* Bosnia and Herzegovina \u2013 ACC, on all tolled highways\n* Bulgaria \u2013 TollPass, on all [[Highways in Bulgaria | highways]] and first class roads for vehicles above 3.5 tons<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tollpass.bg/en/toll/toll-system-in-bulgaria|title=Toll System in Bulgaria|website=www.tollpass.bg}}</ref>\n* Croatia \u2013 ENC, on all tolled [[highways in Croatia]] (''autocesta'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hac.hr/index.php?task=ces&stask=14|title=Home - HAC.hr|website=www.hac.hr}}</ref>\n* Czech Republic \u2013 [[premid]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.premid.cz/index.php?id=291&L=0|title=Rozcestnk|website=www.premid.cz}}</ref> for trucks on [[highway]]s\n* Hungary \u2013 HU-GO,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hu-go.hu|title=HU-GO ELEKTRONIKUS \u00daTD\u00cdJSZED\u00c9SI RENDSZER|website=www.hu-go.hu}}</ref> on all [[highways in Hungary]] for any vehicle\n* Poland \u2013 [[viaTOLL]] mandatory for trucks over 3.5 tons and buses, optional for passenger cars<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.viatoll.pl/en|title=Home - viaTOLL|website=www.viatoll.pl}}</ref>\n* Romania \u2013 [[eTarif - Peaj, eRovinieta road tax]] mandatory for all automobiles <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uti.eu.com/business-lines/intelligent-transportation-solutions/fare-collection/highway-tolling/|title=UTI|website=uti.eu.com}}</ref>\n* Russia \u2013 Flow+ (on [[Western Rapid Diameter]], [[Saint Petersburg]] cross-city express motorway), Avtodor (on high-speed toll [[Moscow\u2013Saint Petersburg motorway]] and toll shortcuts on [[M4 highway (Russia)|M4 highway]])\n* Serbia \u2013 ENP, on all tolled [[highways in Serbia]]\n* [[Road tax and toll in Slovakia|Slovak Republic]] \u2013 SkyToll a. s.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.emyto.sk/web/guest/home |title=Archived copy |access-date=2010-01-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120302104547/https://www.emyto.sk/web/guest/home |archive-date=2012-03-02 |url-status=dead }}</ref> for vehicles over 3.5 tons total weight\n* Slovenia \u2013 ABC\n* Turkey \u2013 [[OGS (electronic toll collection)|OGS]] (active onboard transponder, abbreviation for \"Otomatik Gecis Sistemi\"), [[KGS (electronic toll collection)|KGS]] (smart card, abbreviation for \"Kartli Gecis Sistemi\") for toll roads and toll bridges, [[HGS (electronic toll collection)|HGS]] (passive RFID, abbreviation for \"Hizli Gecis Sistemi\")\n\n== North America ==\n\n=== Canada ===\n* [[Maritime Provinces]]\n** [[MACPASS]] in the [[Halifax, Nova Scotia|Halifax Regional Municipality, Nova Scotia]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.macpass.com/|title=Macpass \u2013 Halifax Harbour Bridges|website=www.macpass.com}}</ref>\n** E-Pass at the [[Cobequid Pass]], [[Cumberland County, Nova Scotia]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.cobequidpass.com/ |title=Cobequid Pass Hwy 104 |access-date=2012-06-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120504002346/http://www.cobequidpass.com/ |archive-date=2012-05-04 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n** Strait Pass at the [[Confederation Bridge]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.straitpass.com/|title=Home|website=www.straitpass.com}}</ref>\n* [[Ontario]]\n** [[Ontario Highway 407|407 ETR/Highway 407E]] and [[Ontario Highway 412|Highway 412]] in the [[Greater Toronto Area]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.407etr.com/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=2008-05-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080509173717/http://www.407etr.com/ |archive-date=2008-05-09 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://highway407east.com/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=2018-08-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171207210821/http://www.highway407east.com/ |archive-date=2017-12-07 |url-status=dead }}</ref> <!-- tolling on Ontario Highway 407/412 to begin in 2017 -->\n** [[HOT Lanes]] on given [[400-series highways]] like the [[Queen Elizabeth Way]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/transportation/2016/06/23/toll-lanes-coming-to-qew-on-sept-15.html|title=Solo drivers get shot at HOT lanes \u2014 for a price - The Star|publisher=}}</ref>\n** [[E-ZPass]] at the [[Peace Bridge]] and the [[Lewiston\u2013Queenston Bridge]]\n*[[Quebec]]\n** Le lien intelligent at the [[Olivier-Charbonneau Bridge]] ([[Quebec Autoroute 25|autoroute 25]]) crossing the [[Rivi\u00e8re des Prairies]] in Montreal<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.a25.com/|title=Le Lien Intelligent - Le Pont de l'A25|last=A25|website=www.a25.com}}</ref>\n** A30 Express at the Pont Serge-Marcil ([[Quebec Autoroute 30|autoroute 30]]) crossing the [[Saint Lawrence River]] in the Montreal area<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.a30express.com/|title=A30|website=www.a30express.com}}</ref>\n\n=== Costa Rica ===\n* Quick Pass<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bac.net/bacsanjose/esp/banco/promociones/quickpassBACF.html|archive-url=https://archive.today/20121220065926/https://www.bac.net/bacsanjose/esp/banco/promociones/quickpassBACF.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=2012-12-20|title=Quick Pass|publisher=}}</ref> lane uses E-Z Pass technology in all toll booths in the country.\n\n=== Dominican Republic ===\n* Paso Rapido<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pasorapido.gob.do/|title=Paso Rapido|publisher=}}</ref> lane uses E-Z Pass technology in all toll booths in the country.\n\n=== Mexico ===\n* IAVE<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.e-mexico.gob.mx/wb2/eMex/eMex_Tarjeta_IAVE|title=IAVE|publisher=|access-date=2008-07-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080521021806/http://www.e-mexico.gob.mx/wb2/eMex/eMex_Tarjeta_IAVE|archive-date=2008-05-21|url-status=dead}}</ref> is used on all the highways operated by [[Caminos y Puentes Federales]] (CAPUFE).\n\n=== United States ===\nThe 2012 transportation funding bill [[Moving Ahead for Progress in the 21st Century Act|MAP-21]] required all electronic tolling systems on Interstate highways be compatible by October 1, 2016, but no funding and no penalty were provided, so discussions on interoperability are ongoing<ref name=\"ajc\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ajc.com/news/local/gridlock-guy-linking-all-states-toll-roads-not-easy/CfYNrc181RosssgnjEiVCI/|title=Gridlock Guy: Linking all states' toll roads not easy|publisher=}}</ref> through the International Bridge, Tunnel and Turnpike Association.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nj.com/traffic/index.ssf/2017/05/when_will_you_be_able_to_use_your_e-zpass_nationwide.html|title=When will you be able to use your E-ZPass nationwide?|publisher=}}</ref>\nIn [[Florida]], older battery-powered SunPass transponders were no longer accepted as of January 1, 2016, in preparation for future compatibility with E-ZPass toll booths. Several [[US Mobile Tolling Platforms|mobile tolling platforms]] are currently in use.\n\n*'''[[AutoExpreso]]''' in [[Puerto Rico]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.autoexpreso.com/|title=Bienvenido a AutoExpreso|website=www.autoexpreso.com}}</ref>\n*'''Downbeach Express Pass''' on the [[County Route 563 (New Jersey)|Downbeach Express]] in [[New Jersey]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.downbeachexpress.com/Home_Page.html|title=Downbeach Express|website=downbeachexpress}}</ref>\n*'''[[E-PASS]]''' (Florida)\n**Interoperable with:\n***North Carolina '''Quick Pass'''\n***Georgia '''PeachPass'''\n***Florida '''SunPass'''\n*'''E-PASS Xtra''' (expanded E-PASS)\n**Interoperable with:\n***Florida '''E-PASS'''\n***Florida '''SunPass'''\n***Georgia '''PeachPass'''\n***North Carolina '''Quick Pass'''\n***'''E-ZPass'''\n***Illinois '''I-Pass'''\n***Louisville '''RiverLink'''\n*'''[[E-ZPass]]''' network ([[Delaware]], [[Illinois]], [[Indiana]], [[Kentucky]], [[Maine]], [[Maryland]], [[Massachusetts]], [[New Hampshire]], [[New Jersey]], [[New York (state)|New York]], [[North Carolina]], [[Ohio]], [[Pennsylvania]], [[Rhode Island]], [[Virginia]], [[West Virginia]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ezpassmaineturnpike.com/|title=Welcome to the Maine Turnpike's E-ZPass Program|website=www.ezpassmaineturnpike.com}}</ref>\n**'''[[I-Pass]]''' in [[Illinois]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.illinoistollway.com/|title=Home - Illinois Tollway|website=www.illinoistollway.com}}</ref>\n**'''[[NC Quick Pass]]''' in [[North Carolina]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.myncquickpass.com/en/home/index.shtml |title=Archived copy |access-date=2012-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121011043551/https://www.myncquickpass.com/en/home/index.shtml |archive-date=2012-10-11 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n**'''RiverLink''' system in [[Indiana]] and [[Kentucky]] for bridges over the [[Ohio River]] in the [[Louisville, Kentucky|Louisville]] metro area. These presently include the formerly toll-free [[John F. Kennedy Bridge]] for southbound [[Interstate 65|I-65]], the [[Abraham Lincoln Bridge]] on northbound I-65, and the [[Lewis and Clark Bridge (Ohio River)|Lewis and Clark Bridge]] (including the East End Tunnel on the Kentucky approach) on IN&nbsp;265/KY&nbsp;841 (future extension of [[Interstate 265|I-265]] in both states). Motorists can obtain an E-ZPass transponder or a non-interoperable RiverLink one for use on RiverLink facilities only.\n**The E-ZPass system was branded as [[I-Zoom]] on the [[Indiana Toll Road]] from 2007 to 2012.\n**In [[Massachusetts]], the E-ZPass system was branded as [[Fast Lane (E-ZPass)|Fast Lane]] between 1998 and 2012. As of 2016, all toll facilities in Massachusetts use open-road tolling, and customers without transponders are charged a higher pay-by-plate rate.\n**Additionally, there are E-ZPass lanes in [[Ontario]], [[Canada]] at the [[Peace Bridge]] (Canada-bound direction only) and the [[Lewiston-Queenston Bridge]]; these are the only E-ZPass toll booths outside of the United States.\n**[[E-PASS|E-PASS Xtra]] booths in [[Orlando, Florida]] as of September 1, 2018, but only on roads operated by [[Central Florida Expressway Authority]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.cfxway.com/agency-information/newsroom/news-releases/central-florida-expressway-authority-joins-e-zpass-group/ | title=CFX}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.wftv.com/traffic/e-zpass-will-work-on-some-local-toll-roads-starting-sept-1/804447556 | title=E-ZPass is coming to some local toll roads starting Sept. 1| date=2018-08-02}}</ref>\n*'''Express Pass''' in [[Utah]], for the [[Interstate 15 in Utah|I-15]] [[High-occupancy toll lane|HOT lanes]] in the [[Salt Lake City]] area<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.udot.utah.gov/ExpressLanes/Home/ExpressPass|title=Express Lanes|website=www.udot.utah.gov|language=en|access-date=2018-10-05}}</ref>\n*'''[[EXpressToll]]''' network in [[Colorado]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.expresstoll.com/|title=ExpressToll|website=www.expresstoll.com}}</ref>\n**GO-PASS on [[Northwest Parkway]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.northwestparkway.org|title=Northwest Parkway|website=www.northwestparkway.org}}</ref>\n*'''[[FasTrak]]''' in [[California]]<ref>[https://www.bayareafastrak.org/en/home/index.shtml]</ref>\n* Florida-Georgia-North Carolina interoperability area (Florida Turnpike Enterprise, Central Florida Expressway Authority)\n*'''Freedom Pass''' in [[Alabama]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://freedompass.americanroads.com/|title=Alabama Freedom Pass Online - Login|website=freedompass.americanroads.com}}</ref> at the following locations:\n**Tuscaloosa Bypass\n**Montgomery Expressway\n**Emerald Mountain Expressway\n**Beach Express\n*'''[[GeauxPass (Louisiana)|GeauxPass]]''' in [[Louisiana]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dotd.state.la.us/operations/cccd/toll_tags.asp|title=LaDOTD|website=www.dotd.state.la.us}}</ref>\n*'''[[Good to Go (toll collection system)|Good to Go]]''' in [[Washington (state)|Washington state]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wsdot.wa.gov/GoodToGo/|title=Good To Go! - Official WSDOT website - WSDOT|website=www.wsdot.wa.gov}}</ref>\n*'''[[MnPass]]''' in [[Minnesota]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dot.state.mn.us/information/mnpass/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=2008-05-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080209230431/http://www.dot.state.mn.us/information/mnpass/ |archive-date=2008-02-09 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*'''[[NationalPass]]''', a system for providing a single transponder claimed to be compatible with all of the other systems listed here.\n*'''Nexpress Toll''' in [[Michigan]] at the [[Detroit-Windsor Tunnel]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://secure.dwtunnel.com/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=2011-08-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120118214435/https://secure.dwtunnel.com/ |archive-date=2012-01-18 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*'''[[Palmetto Pass]]''' in [[South Carolina]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.crossislandparkway.org/index.html |title=Welcome to the South Carolina Palmetto Pass Website! |access-date=2012-12-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120108233101/http://www.crossislandparkway.org/index.html |archive-date=2012-01-08 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*'''[[Peach Pass]]''' in [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.peachpass.com/|title=Peach Pass \u2013 Keep Moving with Peach Pass|website=www.peachpass.com}}</ref>\n*'''[[SunPass]]''' network ([[Florida]])\n**[[LeeWay]], [[Lee County, Florida]]\n**[[O-PASS]], [[Osceola County, Florida]]\n**[[C-Pass]] in [[Key Biscayne, Florida]] was replaced by SunPass and pay-by-plate on September 23, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://miami.cbslocal.com/2014/09/17/rickenbacker-venetian-causeway-tolls-convert-to-sunpass/|title=Rickenbacker & Venetian Causeway Tolls Convert To SunPass|date=17 September 2014|publisher=}}</ref>\n****'''[[Peach Pass]]''' in [[Atlanta|Atlanta, Georgia]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.peachpass.com/|title=Peach Pass \u2013 Keep Moving with Peach Pass|website=www.peachpass.com}}</ref>\n****Also interoperable with North Carolina '''Quick Pass,''' Florida '''E-PASS,''' and Florida '''SunPass'''.  Not interoperable with other E-Z Pass systems.  (For many northeastern toll booths, this would require adding equipment to read the newer Georgia transponders and add video cameras to support Florida pay-by-plate drivers.)<ref name=\"ajc\" />\n* Texas-Oklahoma-Kansas interoperability area (North Texas Tollway Authority hub)\n**'''[[TxTAG]]''' network ([[Texas]])<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.txtag.org/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=2008-05-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080514103849/http://www.txtag.org/ |archive-date=2008-05-14 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n***[[TollTag]] in [[Dallas|Dallas, Texas]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ntta.org/|title=NTTA Home|website=www.ntta.org}}</ref>\n***[[EZ TAG]] in [[Houston|Houston, Texas]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.hctra.com/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=2008-05-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070530211936/http://www.hctra.com/ |archive-date=2007-05-30 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n**'''[[Pikepass]]''' in [[Oklahoma]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pikepass.com|title=PIKEPASS: Faster. Safer. Easier|website=www.pikepass.com}}</ref>\n**'''[[Kansas Turnpike#Tolls|K-Tag]]''' in [[Kansas]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ksturnpike.com/|title=Kansas Turnpike Authority|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n== Australia ==\n\n=== Australia ===\n{{Main|e-TAG}}\n* [[Airport Link, Brisbane|Airport Link Tunnel]] in [[Brisbane]], [[Queensland]]\n* [[Clem Jones Tunnel]] (Clem7) in Brisbane\n* [[Gateway Motorway]] in Brisbane\n* [[Go Between Bridge]] in Brisbane\n* [[Logan Motorway]] in Brisbane\n* [[Legacy Way]] Tunnel in Brisbane\n* [[CityLink]], in [[Melbourne]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]]\n* [[EastLink, Melbourne|Eastlink]], in Melbourne\n* [[Sydney Harbour Bridge]] and [[Sydney Harbour Tunnel]], in [[Sydney]], [[New South Wales]]\n* [[Eastern Distributor]] in Sydney\n* [[M2 Hills Motorway]], in Sydney\n* [[M4 Western Motorway]], in Sydney\n* [[M5 South Western Motorway]], in Sydney\n* [[Westlink M7]], in Sydney\n* [[Cross City Tunnel]], in Sydney\n* [[Lane Cove Tunnel]], in Sydney\n\n=== New Zealand ===\n* Northern Gateway Toll Road on the [[Auckland Northern Motorway|Northern Motorway]] in [[Auckland]]\n* Tauranga Eastern Link Toll Road on State highway 2 in Tauranga\n* Takitimu Drive Toll road on State highway 29 in Tauranga\n\n== South America ==\n\n=== Argentina ===\n* Autopistas Avenida General Paz and Acceso Norte in [[Buenos Aires]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ausol.com.ar/|title=Autopistas del Sol|website=www.ausol.com.ar}}</ref> system PASE (Peaje Autom\u00e1tico Sin Espera)\n* Autopistas 25 de Mayo, Dellepiane, Perito Moreno and Arturo Illia<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ausa.com.ar/|title=Concesionaria AUSA|publisher=}}</ref>\n* Autopista Ezeiza \u2013 Ca\u00f1uelas<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ohlconcesiones.com/html/espanol/aecsa.html|title=AECSA/OHL Concesiones|access-date=2008-05-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080405213255/http://www.ohlconcesiones.com/html/espanol/aecsa.html|archive-date=2008-04-05|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* Autopista Acceso Oeste<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.auoeste.com.ar/|title=-- Autopistas del Oeste --|website=www.auoeste.com.ar}}</ref>\n* Autopista La Plata \u2013 Buenos Aires<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.au-laplata.com.ar/|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20070925141758/http://www.au-laplata.com.ar/|url-status=dead|title=Autopista La Plata Buenos Aires --|date=25 September 2007|archivedate=25 September 2007}}</ref>\n* Autopista Camino Parque del Buen Ayre<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ceamse.gov.ar/|title=CEAMSE ecolog\u00eda urbana - \u00e1rea metropolitana|website=www.ceamse.gov.ar}}</ref>\n* C\u00f3rdoba \u2013 Caminos de las sierras (CUIS)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.camsierras.com.ar/|title=Web Server's Default Page|website=www.camsierras.com.ar}}</ref>\n\n=== Chile ===\n* Autopista Central<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.autopistacentral.cl/|title=Autopista Central|author=|date=|website=autopistacentral.cl|accessdate=15 May 2019}}</ref> in [[Santiago, Chile|Santiago]]\n* Autopista Vespucio Sur<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vespuciosur.cl/|title=Vespucio Sur|website=www.vespuciosur.cl}}</ref> in Santiago\n* Autopista Vespucio Norte Express<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vespucioexpress.cl/|title=Autopista Vespucio Norte \u2013 Solicitar Tag, Pase Diario y pago en l\u00ednea.|website=www.vespucioexpress.cl|access-date=2018-06-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181023153120/http://www.vespucioexpress.cl/|archive-date=2018-10-23|url-status=dead}}</ref> in Santiago\n* Costanera Norte<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cnorte.cl/|title=Costanera Norte|author=|date=|website=web.costaneranorte.cl|accessdate=15 May 2019}}</ref> in Santiago (world's first free-flow ETC freeway to cross through a downtown area)\n* T\u00fanel San Crist\u00f3bal<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tunelsancristobal.cl/|title=T\u00fanel San Crist\u00f3bal \u2013 Informaci\u00f3n sobre la ruta, tag y pago en l\u00ednea|author=|date=|website=tunelsancristobal.cl|accessdate=15 May 2019}}</ref> in Santiago\n* Acceso Sur de Santiago and Chile Highway 5 Santiago \u2013 Talca section<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rutamaipo.cl/|title=Ruta Maipo|website=www.rutamaipo.cl}}</ref>\n* Chile Route 68<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rutasdelpacifico.cl/|title=Rutas del Pac\u00edfico - an Abertis Company|website=www.rutasdelpacifico.cl}}</ref> in Santiago \u2013 Valpara\u00edso and Santiago Vi\u00f1a del Mar\n* International Highway Los Libertadores<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ohlconcesiones.cl/autopistaloslibertadores/|title=International Highway Los Libertadores|publisher=}}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> (Chilean section)\n* Arturo Merino Benitez Road Access<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.accesovialamb.cl/|title=Acceso Vial AMB|website=www.accesovialamb.cl}}</ref> in Santiago\n\n''See also'': [[Open road tolling|Free-flow]]\n\n=== Colombia ===\n* Vial Del Valle in [[Cali]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.calccit.org/itsdecision/serv_and_tech/Electronic_toll_collection/electron_toll_collection_report.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2008-05-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080516121229/http://www.calccit.org/itsdecision/serv_and_tech/Electronic_toll_collection/electron_toll_collection_report.html#colo |archive-date=2008-05-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n== Africa ==\n\n=== South Africa ===\n* [[e-toll (South Africa)|e-toll]] operated by Sanral<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sanral.co.za/e-toll/ |title=Sanral |access-date=2013-10-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023134035/http://www.sanral.co.za/e-toll/ |archive-date=2013-10-23 |url-status=dead }}</ref> throughout the [[Gauteng]] province. Cities include Johannesburg, Pretoria, Centurion, Midrand, Soweto and the East and West Rand.\n* Bakwena N1N4 Toll Concession<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bakwena.co.za/|title=Home - Bakwena N1N4 toll|website=Bakwena N1N4 toll}}</ref> The Bakwena N1N4 Toll is a separate system and has been operating for the past 12 years. The e-tag system employed by [[South African National Roads Agency|Sanral]] is also compatible with the current Bakwena tags and may be registered with Sanral's e-toll system for use on certain sections of the N1 and N4 towards Bela-Bela, Rustenburg and Botswana.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bakwena.co.za/?menu=news&option=119|title=Home - Bakwena N1N4 toll|website=Bakwena N1N4 toll}}</ref>\n*Since December 2015, the e-tag is operational on all toll roads nationally.<ref>{{cite web|last=Reporter |first=Staff |url=https://www.techcentral.co.za/e-tags-now-accepted-nationally/61850/ |title=E-tags now accepted nationally |publisher=TechCentral |date=2015-12-04 |accessdate=2018-06-02}}</ref>\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.tolltickets.com/country/europe/europe.aspx?lang=en-GB Overview of European tolling systems]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n[[Category:Toll roads|*]]\n[[Category:Electronic toll collection|*]]\n[[Category:Road transport-related lists|Electronic Toll]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThis is a '''list of [[electronic toll collection]] systems''' in use on [[toll road]]s throughout the world.\n{{inc-transport|date=August 2008}}\n\n{{TOC right}}\n\n== Asia ==\n\n=== East Asia ===\n\n===== China =====\nETC has operated since June 2014. 13 provinces support ETC as of December 2014. As of December 2015, it works in 29 provinces. Plans vary by province and bank, and discounted rates (usually 5% off) may be available in some areas. The [[Ministry of Transport of the People's Republic of China|MoT]] scheduled to cancel all cross-provinces and cross-junctions toll booths in 2019, by renovating toll booths in all entries and exists, plus installing barrels (like how Electronic Road Pricing in Singapore works) on the province borders to fully support non-stop payments, and hence all such toll booths are cancelled by Jan 1, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mot.gov.cn/zhuanti/shoufeiglzdgg/|title=\u6df1\u5316\u6536\u8d39\u516c\u8def\u5236\u5ea6\u6539\u9769 \u53d6\u6d88\u9ad8\u901f\u516c\u8def\u7701\u754c\u6536\u8d39\u7ad9|author=[[Ministry of Transport of the People's Republic of China]]|accessdate=13 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nType of payment: prepaid card, some Chinese debit card (depends on at which bank one's ETC was opened), some Chinese credit cards (depends on at which bank one's ETC was opened), and (in some provinces) [[Alipay]] and [[WeChat|WeChat pay]]. There usually an up front payment for new users. Wherever the Chinese ETC is opened, it is accepted nationwide as long as ETC is supported in that area.\n\nSome emergency services vehicles, such as [[fire truck]]s and military vehicles, are also installed ETC e-tags by [[Ministry of Emergency Management|MEM]] and [[Ministry of National Defense of the People's Republic of China|MND]].\n\n{| border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" cellpadding=\"2\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse;\"\n|+\n|- style=\"background:#069;\"\n|'''<span style=\"color:white;\">Name of roadway</span>'''\n|'''<span style=\"color:white;\">Type of roadway</span>'''\n|'''<span style=\"color:white;\">Owned by</span>'''\n|'''<span style=\"color:white;\">Operated by</span>'''\n|'''<span style=\"color:white;\">Location</span>'''\n|-\n|Huitong Card\n| rowspan=\"23\" |Expressways\nToll roads\n\nParking places\n\nCustom checkpoints\n|Anhui Government\n|Anhui Province Expressway Network Operation Co Ltd\n|[[Anhui]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Sutong Card\n| Beijing Government\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Beijing Sutong Technology Co Ltd\n|[[Beijing]]\n|-\n|Tianjin Government\n|[[Tianjin]]\n|-\n| Tongyu Card\n|Chongqing Government\n|Chongqing Expressways Corp.\n|[[Chongqing]]\n|-\n|Mintong Card\n|Fujian Government\n|Fujian Expressway ETC toll center\n|[[Fujian]]\n|-\n|E-Serve\n|Guangdong Government\n|Guangdong Unitoll Co Ltd\n|[[Guangdong-Hong Kong-Macau Greater Bay Area|GD-HK-MO]]\n|-\n|Baguixing Card\n|Guangxi Government\n|Guangxi Jietong Expressway Technology Co Ltd\n|[[Guangxi]]\n|-\n|Low Carbon Driving Card\n|Hebei Government\n|Hebei Expressway Bureau\n|[[Hebei]]\n|-\n|Zhongyuantong\n|Henan Government\n|Henan Shibo Electronic Co Ltd\n|[[Henan]]\n|-\n|Heilongjiang ETC Card\n|Heilongjiang Government\n|Heilongjiang ETC Bureau\n|[[Heilongjiang]]\n|-\n|Hubei ETC VIP\n|Hubei Government\n|Hubei Expressway Network Toll collecting Center\n|[[Hubei]]\n|-\n|Xiangtong Card\n|Hunan Government\n|Hunan Expressway Jietong Informations Co Ltd\n|[[Hunan]]\n|-\n|Mengtong Card\n|Inner Mongolia Government\n|\n|[[Inner Mongolia]]\n|-\n|Sutong Card\n|Jiangsu Government\n|Jiangsu Expressway Network Operation Co Ltd\n|[[Jiangsu]]\n|-\n|Gantong Card\n|Jiangxi Government\n|Jiangxi Expressway Networking Management Center\n|[[Jiangxi]]\n|-\n|\n|Jilin Government\n|\n|[[Jilin]]\n|-\n|\n|Liaoning Government\n|Liaoning Province Expressway Industrial Development Co Ltd\n|[[Liaoning]]\n|-\n|Sanqintong\n|Shaanxi Government\n|Shaanxi Province Expressway E-pay Co Ltd\n|[[Shaanxi]]\n|-\n|Lutong Card\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Shandong Government\n|Shandong Expressway Collecting Center\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Shandong]]\n|-\n|Xinlian Card\n|Shandong Expressway Xinlian Co Ltd\n|-\n|Hutong Card\n|Shanghai Government\n|SPTCC\n|[[Shanghai]]\n|-\n|Kuaitong Card\n|Shanxi Government\n|Shanxi Transportation Informations Co Ltd\n|[[Shanxi]]\n|-\n|Zhejiang ETC Card\n|Zhejiang Government\n|Zhejiang Highway Bureau\n|[[Zhejiang]]\n|}\nNote that there's no known payment systems and toll booths for expressways in [[Hainan]] and [[Tibet Autonomous Region|Tibet]], because:\n\n# Management fees of Hainan expressways are combined with fuel surcharges, and hence instead of paying by drivers, such fees are dynamically paid by [[filling station]]s in Hainan;\n# Expressways in Tibet are builded by Tibetan [[People's Armed Police|PAP]]<nowiki/>s, and are directly managed by [[State Council of the People's Republic of China|State Council]].\n\n===== Hong Kong =====\n{{main|Autotoll}}\nCovers toll roads and tunnels in Hong Kong; 220,000 users making 320,000 daily transactions.\n{| border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" cellpadding=\"2\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse;\"\n|+\n|- style=\"background:#069;\"\n|'''<span style=\"color:white;\">Name of roadway</span>'''\n|'''<span style=\"color:white;\">Type of roadway</span>'''\n|'''<span style=\"color:white;\">Owned by</span>'''\n|'''<span style=\"color:white;\">Operated by</span>'''\n|'''<span style=\"color:white;\">Location</span>'''\n|-\n|\n| 12 toll roads and tunnels\n|\n| Autotoll (Autopass (now merged with Autotoll) and Electronic Toll Systems Ltd. (now merged with Autotoll)\n| [[Hong Kong]]\n|}\n\n==== Japan ====\nETC started operation in 2001. It covers toll roads and tunnels in Japan; there are 6,000,000 daily transactions with a usage ratio of 90%.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.go-etc.jp/english/index.html|title=ETC portal site|website=www.go-etc.jp|access-date=2013-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090830070147/http://www.go-etc.jp/english/index.html|archive-date=2009-08-30|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==== South Korea ====\n[[hi-pass]], operated by [[Korea Expressway Corporation]], covers all [[Expressways in South Korea|national express roads]] and several BTO/BTL roads in South Korea. From 2013, transportation cards the (T-money, Cashbee, and Hanpay) are compatible with existing hi-pass system.\n\n==== Taiwan ====\n{{main|Electronic Toll Collection (Taiwan)}}\nTaiwan's ETC systems have been  operating since February 10, 2006. It transitioned from OBU (infrared-based) to e-Tag (passive RFID-based) MLFF as of 2012, and started live operations in December 2013.\n\n{| border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" cellpadding=\"2\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse;\"\n|+\n|- style=\"background:#069;\"\n|'''<span style=\"color:white;\">Name of roadway</span>'''\n|'''<span style=\"color:white;\">Type of roadway</span>'''\n|'''<span style=\"color:white;\">Owned by</span>'''\n|'''<span style=\"color:white;\">Operated by</span>'''\n|'''<span style=\"color:white;\">Location</span>'''\n|-\n| [[National Freeway 1|Sun Yat-sen Freeway]], [[National Freeway 3|Formosa Freeway]] (21 toll stations)\n| Highway\n|Taiwan Area Freeway Bureau\n|Far Eastern Electronic Toll Collection Co. (FETC)\n|\n|}\n\n=== Southwest Asia ===\n{| border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" cellpadding=\"2\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse;\"\n|+\n|- style=\"background:#069;\"\n|'''<span style=\"color:white;\">Name of roadway</span>'''\n|'''<span style=\"color:white;\">Type of roadway</span>'''\n|'''<span style=\"color:white;\">Owned by</span>'''\n|'''<span style=\"color:white;\">Operated by</span>'''\n|'''<span style=\"color:white;\">Location</span>'''\n|-\n| [[Highway 6 (Israel)|Highway 6]]\n| Highway\n|\n| [[Derech Eretz]]\n| [[Israel]]\n|-\n| Shaikh Zayed Road\n| Highway\n|\n| [[Transportation in Dubai|RTA]]\n| [[Dubai]], [[UAE]]\n|-\n| [[Salik (road toll)|Salik]]\n| ETC\n|\n| [[Transportation in Dubai#Roads|RTA]]\n| [