{"title_page": "Boabeng-Fiema Monkey Sanctuary", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n| official_name                   = Boabeng-Fiema Monkey Sanctuary\n| other_name                      = Boabeng-Fiema Monkey Wildlife Sanctuary\n| settlement_type                 = [[Village]]\n| imagesize                       = 300px\n| pushpin_map                     = Ghana\n| pushpin_label_position          = bottom\n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Ghana\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = [[Image:Flag of Ghana.svg|25px]] [[Ghana]]\n| subdivision_type1               = [[Regions of Ghana|Region]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Brong-Ahafo Region|Brong Ahafo Region]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[Districts of Ghana|District]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Nkoranza North District]]\n| coordinates                     = {{coord|7|43|08|N|1|43|25|W|region:GH|display=inline}}\n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = 366\n| elevation_ft                    = \n\n}}\n\nThe '''Boabeng-Fiema Monkey Wildlife Sanctuary''' is found at Boaben and [[Fiema]], twin communities 22 [[kilometers]] away from the [[Nkoranza North District]] of the [[Bono East Region|Bono East region]], [[Ghana]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.graphic.com.gh/features/features/an-encounter-with-sacred-monkeys.html|title=An encounter with Sacred Monkeys|website=www.graphic.com.gh|access-date=2019-05-18}}</ref> The 4.4 kilometer square (km\u00b2) forest, believed to have been created in the 1970s, houses many trees, [[birds]], [[reptiles]], [[deer]] and [[monkeys]], two of which are the [[Ursine colobus|Geoffrey's Pied Colobus]] and [[Campbell's mona monkey|Campbell Mona monkey]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bradtguides.com/destinations/africa/ghana/boabeng-fiema-monkey-sanctuary.html|title=Boabeng-Fiema Monkey Sanctuary {{!}} Bradt Travel Guides|website=www.bradtguides.com|access-date=2019-05-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://visitghana.com/attractions/brong-ahafo-region/|title=BRONG AHAFO REGION|website=Visit Ghana|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n\nIt is a home for about 700 monkeys. The village is a community where monkeys and human beings live together. The inhabitants in the village always leave food outside their homes for the animals. The monkeys see human beings as their own.<ref name=\"Touring Ghana - Brong Ahafo Region\">[http://www.touringghana.com/regions/brongahafo_region.asp Touring Ghana - Brong Ahafo Region] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120517125823/http://www.touringghana.com/regions/brongahafo_region.asp |date=May 17, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nThe monkeys in the sanctuary are protected by the traditional laws on the area. The sanctuary serves as a national tourist site and is accessible by road.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.myjoyonline.com/news/2016/april-17th/boabeng-fiema-monkey-sanctuary-collapsing-over-poor-road-network.php|title=Boabeng-Fiema Monkey Sanctuary collapsing over poor road network|date=2016-04-17|website=www.myjoyonline.com|access-date=2019-05-18}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{coord|7|43|08|N|1|43|25|W|region:GH-BA_type:landmark_source:kolossus-dewiki|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Brong-Ahafo Region]]\n[[Category:Protected areas of Ghana]]\n\n\n{{Ghana-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n| official_name                   = Boabeng-Fiema Monkey Sanctuary\n| other_name                      = Boabeng-Fiema Monkey Wildlife Sanctuary\n| settlement_type                 = [[Village]]\n| imagesize                       = 300px\n| pushpin_map                     = Ghana\n| pushpin_label_position          = bottom\n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Ghana\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = [[Image:Flag of Ghana.svg|25px]] [[Ghana]]\n| subdivision_type1               = [[Regions of Ghana|Region]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Brong-Ahafo Region|Brong Ahafo Region]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[Districts of Ghana|District]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Nkoranza North District]]\n| coordinates                     = {{coord|7|43|08|N|1|43|25|W|region:GH|display=inline}}\n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = 366\n| elevation_ft                    = \n\n}}\n\nThe '''Boabeng-Fiema Monkey Wildlife Sanctuary''' is found at Boaben and [[Fiema]], twin communities 22 [[kilometers]] away from the [[Nkoranza North District]] of the [[Brong-Ahafo Region|Brong Ahafo Region]], [[Ghana]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.graphic.com.gh/features/features/an-encounter-with-sacred-monkeys.html|title=An encounter with Sacred Monkeys|website=www.graphic.com.gh|access-date=2019-05-18}}</ref> The 4.4 kilometer square (km\u00b2) forest, believed to have been created in the 1970s, houses many trees, [[birds]], [[reptiles]], [[deer]] and [[monkeys]], two of which are the [[Ursine colobus|Geoffrey's Pied Colobus]] and [[Campbell's mona monkey|Campbell Mona monkey]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bradtguides.com/destinations/africa/ghana/boabeng-fiema-monkey-sanctuary.html|title=Boabeng-Fiema Monkey Sanctuary {{!}} Bradt Travel Guides|website=www.bradtguides.com|access-date=2019-05-18}}</ref>\n\nIt is a home for about 700 monkeys. The village is a community where monkeys and human beings live together. The inhabitants in the village always leave food outside their homes for the animals. The monkeys see human beings as their own.<ref name=\"Touring Ghana - Brong Ahafo Region\">[http://www.touringghana.com/regions/brongahafo_region.asp Touring Ghana - Brong Ahafo Region] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120517125823/http://www.touringghana.com/regions/brongahafo_region.asp |date=May 17, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nThe monkeys in the sanctuary are protected by the traditional laws on the area. The sanctuary serves as a national tourist site and is accessible by road.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.myjoyonline.com/news/2016/april-17th/boabeng-fiema-monkey-sanctuary-collapsing-over-poor-road-network.php|title=Boabeng-Fiema Monkey Sanctuary collapsing over poor road network|date=2016-04-17|website=www.myjoyonline.com|access-date=2019-05-18}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{coord|7|43|08|N|1|43|25|W|region:GH-BA_type:landmark_source:kolossus-dewiki|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Brong-Ahafo Region]]\n[[Category:Protected areas of Ghana]]\n\n\n{{Ghana-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Bosomba Amosah", "label": "safe", "comment": "correction made", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boabeng-Fiema_Monkey_Sanctuary"}
